From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: jkaczman <jkzgit@pm.me>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 04:33:40 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] libcamera: make dirty version suffix reproducible

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [OE-specific reproducible build fix]

When libcamera builds from a patched git checkout, gen-version.sh appends a -dirty suffix with the *CURRENT* UTC timestamp.
That makes libcamera.so drift due to a different numerical timestamp in each build.

In upstream Raspberry Pi, src/libcamera/meson.build uses vcs_tag() to regenerate version.cpp on each build.
utils/gen-version.sh is where the dirty-tree timestamp is appended
---
 utils/gen-version.sh | 8 +++++++-
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/utils/gen-version.sh b/utils/gen-version.sh
index 6e83074..20514dc 100755
--- a/utils/gen-version.sh
+++ b/utils/gen-version.sh
@@ -42,7 +42,13 @@ if [ -z "$build_dir" ] || (echo "$build_dir" | grep -q "$src_dir")
 then
 	git update-index --refresh > /dev/null 2>&1
 fi
-git diff-index --quiet HEAD || version="$version-dirty ($(date +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S%Z))"
+
+dirty_suffix='-dirty'
+if [ -n "$SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH" ]; then
+	dirty_timestamp=$(date -u -d "@$SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH" +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SUTC 2>/dev/null)
+	[ -n "$dirty_timestamp" ] && dirty_suffix="$dirty_suffix ($dirty_timestamp)"
+fi
+git diff-index --quiet HEAD || version="$version$dirty_suffix"
 
 # If a project version is provided, use it to replace the version number.
 if [ -n "$project_version" ]
-- 
